{
  "name": "Finesse Training (UR, EitR)",
  "type": "feat",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 1st level, a rogue gains @Compendium[world.elephant-in-the-room-feat-taxes.vOy4Ey89I5sipW8r]{Deft Maneuvers (EitR)} as a bonus feat. In addition, starting at 3rd level, she can select any one weapon group listed under the fighter&rsquo;s Weapon Training class feature. Once this choice is made, it cannot be changed. Whenever she makes a successful melee attack with a finesse weapon or an agile weapon from this group, she adds her Dexterity modifier instead of her Strength modifier to the damage roll. If any effect would prevent the rogue from adding her Strength modifier to the damage roll, she does not add her Dexterity modifier.</p>\n<p>The rogue can select a second weapon group at 11th level and a third at 19th level.</p>",
